See the average in the first (repost) chart above, the SOFR/IOR averaged -8 bps back to 2022. See the chart immediately above, the SOFR/IOR averaged -5 bps.

A ‚Äúnormal‚Äù liquidity environment is one where the SOFR/IOR spread is around -8 to -5 bps. See the last five or six weeks, lots of ‚Äúgreen bars‚Äù (positive SOFR/IOR spread). With some ‚Äúred bars‚Äù interspersed in between. In Wall Street parlance, this spread ‚Äúrandom walks‚Äù so look to the larger trend, not day to day movements.

What the larger trend shows is this measure of liquidity is still ‚Äúworrisome.‚Äù Not a crisis, but worrisome. And note that over the last few months trend is moving toward larger green bars.
